docs {
  ## Delete Physical Count Comment
  ลบความคิดเห็นของ physical-count (soft delete) พร้อมลบไฟล์แนบจาก S3 ก่อน

  Soft-deletes a physical count comment, cleaning up S3 attachments first to prevent orphan files.

  ### Path Parameters
  | Name | Type | Description |
  |------|------|-------------|
  | `bu_code` | string | Business unit code |
  | `id` | string (UUID) | Comment ID |

  ### Headers
  | Name | Required | Description |
  |------|----------|-------------|
  | `Authorization` | Yes | `Bearer {{access_token}}` |
  | `x-app-id` | Yes | `{{x_app_id}}` |

  ### Permissions
  - **Permission key**: `inventory_management.physical_count:update`
  - **Roles**: Purchase

  ### Sample Response
  ```json
  {
    "data": { "id": "019638a6-2a00-7c4f-8e46-9b7a52c80c4d" },
    "paginate": null,
    "status": 200,
    "success": true,
    "message": "Success",
    "timestamp": "2026-04-29T08:30:00.000Z"
  }
  ```

  ### Error Responses
  | Status | When |
  |--------|------|
  | 404 | Comment not found |
  | 403 | User lacks `inventory_management.physical_count:update` permission |
  > Service-layer errors propagate via TCP; see micro-business for full list.
}
